<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="66" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1485,2031]" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,336,1485,1511]" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Male pygofer subtriangular in lateral view, ventral side sinuate, apparently wider than dorsal, laterodorsal angle not produced, laterocaudal margin broadly expanded caudad in upper half followed by a plate-like process strongly produced at caudoventral angle (
<figureCitation box="[845,979,1565,1591]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,191,1802]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,158,1859]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 26. Platytibia ferruginea Ding, male genitala. 16, male genitalia, caudal view; 17, same, left lateral view; 18, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 19, same, left lateral view; 20, anal segment, suspensorium and aedeagus, left lateral view; 21, suspensorium, caudal view; 22, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 23, same, right lateral view; 24, anal segment, caudal view; 25, parameres, caudal view; 26, left paramere, left lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185234/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">Figs 17, 19</figureCitation>
); in caudal aspect pygofer with a platelike process at each side of lateroventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[729,864,1605,1631]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,191,1802]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,158,1859]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 26. Platytibia ferruginea Ding, male genitala. 16, male genitalia, caudal view; 17, same, left lateral view; 18, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 19, same, left lateral view; 20, anal segment, suspensorium and aedeagus, left lateral view; 21, suspensorium, caudal view; 22, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 23, same, right lateral view; 24, anal segment, caudal view; 25, parameres, caudal view; 26, left paramere, left lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185234/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">Figs 16, 18</figureCitation>
). Parameres rather broad, surpassing ventral side of anal segment (
<figureCitation box="[359,448,1645,1671]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,191,1802]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,158,1859]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 26. Platytibia ferruginea Ding, male genitala. 16, male genitalia, caudal view; 17, same, left lateral view; 18, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 19, same, left lateral view; 20, anal segment, suspensorium and aedeagus, left lateral view; 21, suspensorium, caudal view; 22, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 23, same, right lateral view; 24, anal segment, caudal view; 25, parameres, caudal view; 26, left paramere, left lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185234/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number box="[416,448,1645,1671]" pageId="4" pageNumber="66" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
), contiguous in basal half, apices rounded and converging, laterally basad of apex expanded laterad, apices converging (
<figureCitation box="[593,681,1685,1711]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,191,1802]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,158,1859]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 26. Platytibia ferruginea Ding, male genitala. 16, male genitalia, caudal view; 17, same, left lateral view; 18, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 19, same, left lateral view; 20, anal segment, suspensorium and aedeagus, left lateral view; 21, suspensorium, caudal view; 22, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 23, same, right lateral view; 24, anal segment, caudal view; 25, parameres, caudal view; 26, left paramere, left lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185234/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number box="[648,681,1685,1711]" pageId="4" pageNumber="66" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus slender, slightly compressed laterally, broad at base, shortly distad of base slightly bent dorsad, apex strongly narrowing, subapex with flag-like flagellum reflected laterobasad, distally curved to right side, with basal spinose process curved to left, phallotreme subapical on dorsal side at base of flagellum (
<figureCitation box="[647,827,1805,1831]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,191,1802]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,158,1859]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 26. Platytibia ferruginea Ding, male genitala. 16, male genitalia, caudal view; 17, same, left lateral view; 18, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 19, same, left lateral view; 20, anal segment, suspensorium and aedeagus, left lateral view; 21, suspensorium, caudal view; 22, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 23, same, right lateral view; 24, anal segment, caudal view; 25, parameres, caudal view; 26, left paramere, left lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185234/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">
Figs 20, 22, 
<number box="[794,827,1805,1831]" pageId="4" pageNumber="66" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
). Genital diaphragm narrow, dorsal margin concave and membranous, medially sclerotized, pigmented, in lateral view with caudally directed process surpassing laterocaudal margin of pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[533,670,1885,1911]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,191,1802]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,158,1859]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 26. Platytibia ferruginea Ding, male genitala. 16, male genitalia, caudal view; 17, same, left lateral view; 18, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 19, same, left lateral view; 20, anal segment, suspensorium and aedeagus, left lateral view; 21, suspensorium, caudal view; 22, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 23, same, right lateral view; 24, anal segment, caudal view; 25, parameres, caudal view; 26, left paramere, left lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185234/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">Figs 18, 19</figureCitation>
). Suspensorium long, articulated with aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1251,1340,1885,1911]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,191,1802]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,158,1859]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 26. Platytibia ferruginea Ding, male genitala. 16, male genitalia, caudal view; 17, same, left lateral view; 18, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 19, same, left lateral view; 20, anal segment, suspensorium and aedeagus, left lateral view; 21, suspensorium, caudal view; 22, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 23, same, right lateral view; 24, anal segment, caudal view; 25, parameres, caudal view; 26, left paramere, left lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185234/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number box="[1307,1340,1885,1911]" pageId="4" pageNumber="66" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
), apparently compressed ventrocaudally, arms short and widely separated, stem nearly 3.0 times as long as arms, basal part narrowed (
<figureCitation box="[397,484,1965,1991]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,191,1802]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,158,1859]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 26. Platytibia ferruginea Ding, male genitala. 16, male genitalia, caudal view; 17, same, left lateral view; 18, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 19, same, left lateral view; 20, anal segment, suspensorium and aedeagus, left lateral view; 21, suspensorium, caudal view; 22, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 23, same, right lateral view; 24, anal segment, caudal view; 25, parameres, caudal view; 26, left paramere, left lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185234/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number box="[451,484,1965,1991]" pageId="4" pageNumber="66" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
). Opening for parameres small, ventral margin evenly arched, lateral and anterior margins nearly straight (
<figureCitation box="[436,523,2005,2031]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,191,1802]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,158,1859]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 26. Platytibia ferruginea Ding, male genitala. 16, male genitalia, caudal view; 17, same, left lateral view; 18, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 19, same, left lateral view; 20, anal segment, suspensorium and aedeagus, left lateral view; 21, suspensorium, caudal view; 22, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 23, same, right lateral view; 24, anal segment, caudal view; 25, parameres, caudal view; 26, left paramere, left lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185234/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number box="[491,523,2005,2031]" pageId="4" pageNumber="66" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
). Anal segment with two blunt, widely spaced processes (
<figureCitation box="[1202,1290,2005,2031]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,191,1802]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,158,1859]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 26. Platytibia ferruginea Ding, male genitala. 16, male genitalia, caudal view; 17, same, left lateral view; 18, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 19, same, left lateral view; 20, anal segment, suspensorium and aedeagus, left lateral view; 21, suspensorium, caudal view; 22, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 23, same, right lateral view; 24, anal segment, caudal view; 25, parameres, caudal view; 26, left paramere, left lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185234/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number box="[1257,1290,2005,2031]" pageId="4" pageNumber="66" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
